eed to preserve that ordering after refactoring.\n\nLooking at the structure more carefully, I need to keep the PM detection and CHANGED_FILES filtering logic, but remove the shared utility functions and environment setup that'll come from the sourced library. The initialization order matters: source the lib first, then set agent-specific variables, then detect the package manager, and finally set up the output directory and lock file.\n\nActually, I'm realizing that only cargo-agent needs the lock setup, while both npm-agent and terra-agent need the output directory. And terra-agent depends on OUTDIR being set before it can define TF_DATA_DIR_PATH, so the setup_outdir call has to come before any environment variables that reference it.\n\nNow I'm going to map out the exact changes needed across all three scripts and start making them.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":23654,"cache_read_input_tokens":38001,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":23654},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6009da08-f492-4e44-8ec1-e3891bd2efc5","uuid":"f18a27b3-02f0-48e4-b6fc-8671bfe9f0ec"}
