{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01UJf1hhwqTsiy9AHMd12btB","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01UvvL3AtK48LQs2tSwLw9iH","name":"Edit","input":{"replace_all":false,"file_path":"/Users/chrisraethke/projects/x-agent/.ralph/exploration.md","old_string":"- `skills/cargo-agent/scripts/cargo-agent.sh`: Rust workflow runner with the heaviest business logic; contains run_x step handlers plus shared boilerplate currently inline.\n- `skills/npm-agent/scripts/npm-agent.sh`: Node workflow runner with package-manager detection and file-scoping logic for lint/format.\n- `skills/terra-agent/scripts/terra-agent.sh`: Terraform workflow runner with safe init/plan behavior and optional tflint checks.","new_string":"- `skills/cargo-agent/scripts/cargo-agent.sh`: Rust workflow runner sourcing `lib/x-agent-common.sh`; contains run_x step handlers and domain-specific helpers (jq diagnostics, package resolution, nextest).\n- `skills/npm-agent/scripts/npm-agent.sh`: Node workflow runner sourcing `lib/x-agent-common.sh`; contains package-manager detection and file-scoping logic for lint/format.\n- `skills/terra-agent/scripts/terra-agent.sh`: Terraform workflow runner sourcing `lib/x-agent-common.sh`; contains safe init/plan behavior and optional tflint checks."},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1545,"cache_read_input_tokens":74905,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1545},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6009da08-f492-4e44-8ec1-e3891bd2efc5","uuid":"02197d2d-5200-4ad4-ab56-e3c8c548c122"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01UvvL3AtK48LQs2tSwLw9iH","type":"tool_result","content":"The file /Users/chrisraethke/projects/x-agent/.ralph/exploration.md has been updated successfully."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6009da08-f492-4e44-8ec1-e3891bd2efc5","uuid":"4afd3a30-ab28-4879-afca-db3ff8bfee4c","tool_use_result":{"filePath":"/Users/chrisraethke/projects/x-agent/.ralph/exploration.md","oldString":"- `skills/cargo-agent/scripts/cargo-agent.sh`: Rust workflow runner with the heaviest business logic; contains run_x step handlers plus shared boilerplate currently inline.\n- `skills/npm-agent/scripts/npm-agent.sh`: Node workflow runner with package-manager detection and file-scoping logic for lint/format.\n- `skills/terra-agent/scripts/terra-agent.sh`: Terraform workflow runner with safe init/plan behavior and optional tflint checks.","newString":"- `skills/cargo-agent/scripts/cargo-agent.sh`: Rust workflow runner sourcing `lib/x-agent-common.sh`; contains run_x step handlers and domain-specific helpers (jq diagnostics, package resolution, nextest).\n- `skills/npm-agent/scripts/npm-agent.sh`: Node workflow runner sourcing `lib/x-agent-common.sh`; contains package-manager detection and file-scoping logic for lint/format.\n- `skills/terra-agent/scripts/terra-agent.sh`: Terraform workflow runner sourcing `lib/x-agent-common.sh`; contains safe init/plan behavior and optional tflint checks.","originalFile":"# x-agent Exploration Notes\n\n## Key Files & Roles\n\n- `lib/x-agent-common.sh`: shared boilerplate for x-agent runners. Provides output helpers, tool validation, output directory/cleanup setup, workflow locking, and summary output helpers. Sourced by every runnable agent script.\n- `skills/cargo-agent/scripts/cargo-agent.sh`: Rust workflow runner with the heaviest business logic; contains run_x step handlers plus shared boilerplate currently inline.\n- `skills/npm-agent/scripts/npm-agent.sh`: Node workflow runner with package-manager detection and file-scoping logic for lint/format.\n- `skills/terra-agent/scripts/terra-agent.sh`: Terraform workflow runner with safe init/plan behavior and optional tflint checks.\n- `tests/run-scenarios.sh`: single orchestrator for shellcheck and fixture execution, including optional filtering by agent/scenario fragment.\n- `tests/*/scenario.env`: declares `SCENARIO_NAME`, `AGENT_SCRIPT`, `RUN_ARGS`, `EXPECT_EXIT`, and `REQUIRED_TOOLS`.\n- `tests/cargo-agent/flock/flock-test.sh`: validates lock wait behavior using a competing holder process and waiting-message assertions.\n- `install.sh`: installs skills, patches paths, and now includes `lib/x-agent-common.sh` for both local/remote install modes.\n- `docs/agents/add-x-agent.md`: canonical structure guide for script boilerplate, helpers, output contract, and agent metadata.\n- `docs/agents/scenario-tests.md` and `docs/testing.md`: fixture contracts and local/CI test flow.\n- `docs/agents/definition-of-done.md`: acceptance checks for output contract, env knobs, and scenario fixtures.\n- `AGENTS.md`: root conventions for Bash 3.2 compatibility, structured output contract, and failure/skip semantics.\n- `.github/workflows/ci.yml`: CI entrypoint that runs `tests/run-scenarios.sh` per agent and optional tool-matrix variants.\n\n## Patterns & Conventions\n\n- Script header pattern: `#!/usr/bin/env bash` + `set -euo pipefail`.\n- Output format is strict and machine-compatible: each step prints `Step:`, `Result: PASS|FAIL|SKIP`, optional `Fix:`, and `Time:`; run end prints `Overall:` and `Logs:`.\n- Runtime knobs are env-overridable: `RUN_<STEP>`, `KEEP_DIR`, `MAX_LINES`, `FAIL_FAST`, `TMPDIR_ROOT`, `CHANGED_FILES`.\n- `FAIL_FAST` uses guarded dispatch: evaluate `should_continue()` before each run step when running `all`.\n- Temp logs flow through `$OUTDIR`; failures and keep-mode preserve temp directory with `Logs kept in: <path>` from trap; success normally removes temp dir.\n- Concurrent invocations are serialized by lockfiles (`${TMPDIR_ROOT}/<agent>.lock`) using `flock` with Perl fallback.\n- `CI` detection switches behavior for line truncation and format checks: CI defaults to `MAX_LINES=999999` and check-only modes where applicable.\n- Optional tools use skip/fallback behavior rather than hard failure; required tools must trigger `exit 2`.\n- Bash compatibility baseline is 3.2: no associative arrays, no `readarray`, no `|&`, no associative case fallthrough.\n\n## Database Schema\n\nNo database is used.\n\n## Test Infrastructure\n\n- `tests/run-scenarios.sh` discovers all `tests/*/scenario.env` fixtures, runs `shellcheck` first (or if filtered), and executes each scenario in fixture directories.\n- Fixture runner expects relative script path via `AGENT_SCRIPT`; missing script prints `SKIP`.\n- If a declared `REQUIRED_TOOLS` item is unavailable, the scenario is `SKIP`.\n- `EXPECT_EXIT` values are asserted; mismatch prints log + first 40 lines.\n- `tests/cargo-agent/flock` adds explicit lock contention coverage; scenario uses `help` mode to keep run short while validating wait message and eventual completion.\n- `tests/run-scenarios.sh --list` enumerates full fixture labels (`tests/<agent>/<case>`), useful to target validation slices.\n- CI runs the same command (`tests/run-scenarios.sh <filter>`) and adds optional matrix variants for `nextest` and `tflint`.\n\n## Architecture & Data Flow\n\n- Entry point: one Bash script per agent called from scenario directory context.\n- Initialization: set defaults (`KEEP_DIR`, `MAX_LINES`, etc.), validate required tools (`need`), allocate output directory, and obtain lock.\n- Execution: parse command args (`--fail-fast`, `help`, and step commands), then route to ordered step functions.\n- Each step runs external tool(s), writes full command output to `$OUTDIR/<step>.log`, and prints an abbreviated result with bounded context lines.\n- Exit path: steps return shell status to an `overall_ok` accumulator; final block prints `Overall` and returns 0/1.\n- Shared-library integration point: each agent script should source `lib/x-agent-common.sh` after `set -euo pipefail` and use `setup_outdir` + `setup_lock` helpers.\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":3,"oldLines":9,"newStart":3,"newLines":9,"lines":[" ## Key Files & Roles"," "," - `lib/x-agent-common.sh`: shared boilerplate for x-agent runners. Provides output helpers, tool validation, output directory/cleanup setup, workflow locking, and summary output helpers. Sourced by every runnable agent script.","-- `skills/cargo-agent/scripts/cargo-agent.sh`: Rust workflow runner with the heaviest business logic; contains run_x step handlers plus shared boilerplate currently inline.","-- `skills/npm-agent/scripts/npm-agent.sh`: Node workflow runner with package-manager detection and file-scoping logic for lint/format.","-- `skills/terra-agent/scripts/terra-agent.sh`: Terraform workflow runner with safe init/plan behavior and optional tflint checks.","+- `skills/cargo-agent/scripts/cargo-agent.sh`: Rust workflow runner sourcing `lib/x-agent-common.sh`; contains run_x step handlers and domain-specific helpers (jq diagnostics, package resolution, nextest).","+- `skills/npm-agent/scripts/npm-agent.sh`: Node workflow runner sourcing `lib/x-agent-common.sh`; contains package-manager detection and file-scoping logic for lint/format.","+- `skills/terra-agent/scripts/terra-agent.sh`: Terraform workflow runner sourcing `lib/x-agent-common.sh`; contains safe init/plan behavior and optional tflint checks."," - `tests/run-scenarios.sh`: single orchestrator for shellcheck and fixture execution, including optional filtering by agent/scenario fragment."," - `tests/*/scenario.env`: declares `SCENARIO_NAME`, `AGENT_SCRIPT`, `RUN_ARGS`, `EXPECT_EXIT`, and `REQUIRED_TOOLS`."," - `tests/cargo-agent/flock/flock-test.sh`: validates lock wait behavior using a competing holder process and waiting-message assertions."]}],"userModified":false,"replaceAll":false}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_019k3pRGJTRRzoC61qc8KvMR","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now create the work summary and run validation:"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":444,"cache_read_input_tokens":76450,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":444},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6009da08-f492-4e44-8ec1-e3891bd2efc5","uuid":"b96df413-55c7-483d-8beb-a7db766faaad"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_019k3pRGJTRRzoC61qc8KvMR","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01C3yrv7up9kYH8E3dtNt19j","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/chrisraethke/projects/x-agent/.ralph/work-summary.txt","content":"# Work Summary — Spec 02: Refactor Existing Agents to Use Shared Library\n\n## What was implemented\n\nRefactored all three existing agents (cargo-agent, npm-agent, terra-agent) to source `lib/x-agent-common.sh` instead of duplicating boilerplate.\n\n### For each agent:\n1. Added `SCRIPT_DIR`/`LIB_DIR` resolution and `source` line after `set -euo pipefail`\n2. Removed duplicated boilerplate: `KEEP_DIR`, `MAX_LINES` (CI-aware block), `FAIL_FAST`, `CHANGED_FILES`, `TMPDIR_ROOT` defaults, `OUTDIR` mktemp, `cleanup()` + trap, `need()`, `hr()`, `should_continue()`, `STEP_START_SECONDS`, `step()`, `fmt_elapsed()`\n3. Replaced inline setup with `setup_outdir \"<agent-name>\"` calls\n4. Replaced inline final summary block with `print_overall \"$overall_ok\"`\n\n### Agent-specific details:\n- **cargo-agent**: Also removed inline lock block (flock + perl fallback), replaced with `setup_lock \"cargo-agent\"`\n- **npm-agent**: No lock block existed; kept `detect_pm()`, `_CHANGED_SRC_FILES` filtering, and all `run_script()` helpers. Added `shellcheck disable=SC2034` for `FAIL_FAST` assignment in `--fail-fast` handler (used by `should_continue()` in shared lib)\n- **terra-agent**: No lock block existed; kept `normalize_dir()`, `resolve_changed_tf_dir()`, `tf()`, `ensure_terraform_project()`, `normalize_fmt_mode()`. `TF_DATA_DIR_PATH` set after `setup_outdir` to ensure `OUTDIR` is available. Added `shellcheck disable=SC2034` for `FAIL_FAST` assignment\n\n## Deviations from work plan\n\n- npm-agent and terra-agent did not need `setup_lock` — they never had lock blocks. Only cargo-agent had workflow locking.\n- Added `shellcheck disable=SC2034` directives for `FAIL_FAST` in npm-agent and terra-agent since shellcheck can't see cross-file usage via sourced library.\n\n## Edge cases handled\n- `FAIL_FAST` shellcheck warning: suppressed with SC2034 directive and comment explaining cross-file usage\n- terra-agent `TF_DATA_DIR_PATH` depends on `OUTDIR`: placed after `setup_outdir` call\n- Agent-specific `RUN_*` variables kept in each agent (not moved to shared lib)\n- `SQLX_OFFLINE` export kept in cargo-agent\n- `JQ_BIN` kept in cargo-agent\n- `detect_pm` and top-level PM echo kept in npm-agent (runs at load time, before main)\n\n## Line count reduction\n- cargo-agent: 658 → 593 (-65 lines, -10%)\n- npm-agent: 390 → 354 (-36 lines, -9%)\n- terra-agent: 469 → 429 (-40 lines, -9%)\n- Total: 1517 → 1376 (-141 lines removed)\n\n## Tests written/run\n- Baseline: all 12 scenarios passed before refactoring\n- After refactor: all 12 scenarios pass (identical results)\n- `shellcheck --severity=warning` passes on all three scripts\n- Shellcheck suite in `tests/run-scenarios.sh` also passes (includes lib/)\n\n## Known limitations\n- `print_result` from shared lib is not adopted by any agent in this spec — agents retain their inline Result/Fix printing patterns because each has unique formatting (cargo's JSON diagnostics, terra's init+plan dual logs, etc.). This is intentional to preserve output parity.\n- Path coupling (`../../../lib`) remains as designed for this phase.\n\n## Exploration notes\nUpdated `.ralph/exploration.md`: changed descriptions for all three agent scripts to note they now source `lib/x-agent-common.sh` instead of containing inline boilerplate.\n\n## Lessons Applied This Phase\nNo prior lessons existed for this project. No new lessons required — refactoring was straightforward with clear patterns.\n\n## Suggestions for the REVIEW agent\n- Verify that the `help` command still works without project context for all three agents\n- The `print_result` function from shared lib remains unused by existing agents — future new agents should adopt it for cleaner step result formatting\n- Lock behavior is only used by cargo-agent; npm-agent and terra-agent don't need locks as they don't have heavy concurrent build semantics\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":444,"cache_read_input_tokens":76450,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":444},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6009da08-f492-4e44-8ec1-e3891bd2efc5","uuid":"dc76849c-70ce-4cf7-a9fe-bd5454cae352"}
